title: Union County fends off Greene County, sets up Rabun County tilt
text:
By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 7: Region title, playoff races take shape after big night VIDEO: Brown, Lanier defense spark Longhorns to tough win over GHS 
BLAIRSVILLE — Union County maintained its spotless record in a 49-28 win over Greene County on Friday in Blairsville. 
The Panthers (7-0, 3-0 Region 8-AA) pulled away with 14 unanswered points in the second quarter for a 28-7 halftime lead. 
Union County running back Bo Lynch rolled up 193 yards rushing and two touchdowns, while quarterback Joseph Mancuso rushed for 110 yds and four scores. Mancuso also completed 11 of 13 passes for 131 yards and one touchdown. 
The win sets up a top 10 and Region 8-AA showdown with Rabun County next week in Tiger. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, Union County football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
